    • InjectedResourceDestructionException

      public InjectedResourceDestructionException(@Nonnull @Nonnull InjectedResource failedResource, @Nullable @Nullable Throwable cause, @Nonnull @RetainedParam @Nonnull @RetainedParam List<@Nonnull InjectedResource> destroyedResources, @Nonnull @RetainedParam @Nonnull @RetainedParam List<@Nonnull InjectedResource> undestroyedResources)
      Constructs an exception with detailed context about the resource destroy failure. This exception provides complete information about the resource that caused the failure, resources that were successfully destroyed before the failure, and resources that remained undestroyed due to the failure.

      Note the resources have already been sorted according to their dependency relationships.

      Parameters:
      failedResource - the resource that failed during destruction, causing the shutdown to abort
      cause - the exception that occurred during the failed resource's destruction
      destroyedResources - the resources that were successfully destroyed before the failure occurred
      undestroyedResources - the resources that were not destroyed due to the abortive termination
